        <body>
            <pb n="1R"/>
            <p rend="align(right)"><placeName>28 West 9<hi rend="underline">th</hi> St. New York
                    City</placeName>.</p>
            <p rend="align(right)"><date>April 10<hi rend="underline">th</hi> 1866</date>.</p>
            <p>
                <addressee>Revd Dr. I. Leeser</addressee>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Rev<hi rend="sup">d</hi> &amp; Dear Sir</p>
            <p rend="indent(2)"><persName>Mr. Sternberger</persName><lb/> having very kindly
                informed me that<lb/> he had mentioned my name to you,<lb/> I embrace the
                opportunity of addressing<lb/> you for the second time, and in<lb/> so doing
                forwarding a letter of<lb/> introduction from <persName>M<hi rend="sup">r</hi>.
                    Sollas</persName> of<lb/>
                <placeName>Jamaica</placeName>. This I had hoped to<lb/> present in person, but will
                not<lb/> be enabled to visit <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName><lb/> for a few
                days. You will<lb/> doubtless recollect the first<lb/> time I had the honor of
                writing<lb/> you,</p>
            <pb n="1V"/>
            <p>you, was in reference to the<lb/> "Guide" a Literary Periodical<lb/> of which I was
                the Editor.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">And now Rev Sir, I beg<lb/> leave to inform you that I<lb/> am in
                search of an appoint,<lb/>ment either as Lecturer, Teacher,<lb/> or Hazan. I feel
                sure if<lb/> you will kindly give me your<lb/> valuable aid &amp; advice, I<lb/>
                shall soon meet with my<lb/> desires. I am well known<lb/> here to the
                        <persName>Rev<hi rend="sup">d</hi> D<hi rend="sup">rs</hi>.
                    Raphael</persName>,<lb/>
                <persName>Isaacs</persName> &amp; <persName>Lyons</persName>. I have already<lb/>
                instituted <sic>enquiries</sic> respecting<lb/> the following appointments<lb/>
                Teacher in <placeName>Memphis Tn</placeName><lb/> " " <placeName>Shreveport
                    La</placeName><lb/> " " <placeName>Norfolk Virg</placeName></p>
            <pb n="2R"/>
            <p>Lecturer in <placeName>Boston Mass.</placeName><lb/> I am told by <persName>Mr.
                    Sternberger</persName><lb/> that there are others of<lb/> which you are
                acquainted<lb/> May I therefore solicit the<lb/> favor of your informing me<lb/> as
                to their directions with<lb/> the necessary particulars.<lb/> In the hope of soon
                seeing<lb/> you and thanking you<lb/> in person<lb/> I am<lb/> Respectfully<lb/>
                Your obt Ser.</p>
            <p>
                <persName role="author">R Dl. Leevier</persName>
            </p>
            <p>Please address<lb/>
                <persName role="author">Rev<hi rend="sup">d</hi>. R. Dl. Leevier</persName><lb/>
                <placeName>28 West 9th St.<lb/> near 6th Avenue<lb/> New Yk.</placeName></p>
        </body>
